<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO INDUSTRY NOTES: SAN DIEGO COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TRW said the previously announced sale of its La Jolla-based TRW LSI Products 
division to KDT Industries has fallen through. As a result, TRW will retain 
ownership of the operation. 
</P>
<P>
TRW LSI employs more than 300 people and manufactures large-scale integrated 
circuits used in medical instrument, broadcast video and defense applications. 
Its Cleveland-based parent said previously that it would divest itself of the 
LSI unit and other electronics operations in a bid to restructure along 
aeronautics, information and automotive product lines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
