<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: CALIFORNIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The investor group that recently signed an agreement to acquire the assets of 
Worlds of Wonder Inc., Fremont, has announced that it plans to name Joshua W. 
Denham president and chief executive of the company it will form to continue 
the operations of Worlds of Wonder. Denham was president of Mattel Electronics 
from 1979 to 1983, and was most recently president of Wonder Products, a 
manufacturer of children's products in Bosler City, La. 
</P>
<P>
After confirmation of the reorganization plan, expected in mid-May, Stephen J. 
Hopkins, who has been president and chief executive of the company since April, 
1988, will return to Connecticut-based Nightingale &amp; Associates Inc., a 
management consulting firm specializing in turning around financially troubled 
companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
