<P>
The Italian film company that co-produced "The Last Emperor" is going to build 
a $17-million film studio in Singapore. Due for completion in about two years, 
the complex will be used for indoor shooting by Cecchi Gori Summit Studios 
(Singapore), a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Italian Cecchi Gori company. 
