<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Buddy Rogers was at the new Gene Autry Western Heritage Museum in 
Griffith Park Wednesday to dedicate the Mary Pickford Education Center and 
Library. The center features three classrooms, a docent library and the 
administrative complex for the Western museum's education department. The 
center was funded by a $225,000 grant from the Mary Pickford Foundation, a 
donation made "because programs at the museum will emphasize the role of women 
and minorities, something about which Mary felt strongly," said Rogers, husband 
of the late film star. He said that only once before has the Mary Pickford 
Foundation awarded funding at that level. A similar amount was given for the 
Mary Pickford Theater at the Library of Congress. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
