<TEXT>
<P>
The Christic Institute, whose lawsuit against several Iran-Contra figures was 
dismissed, posted a $1.2-million surety bond guaranteeing payment of 
defendants' legal costs if the group loses its appeal. U.S. District Judge 
James Lawrence King in Miami dismissed the Washington-based public interest law 
firm's $23.8-million lawsuit last June 23, four days before the trial was 
scheduled to begin. He ordered the group Feb. 2 to pay $1 million in legal fees 
and costs to 14 defendants. The $1.2-million surety bond covers the defendants' 
previous legal costs and appeals costs and fees if the group loses its appeal 
of King's ruling. 
</P>
