<TEXT>
<P>
A 27-year-old Marine collapsed and died during a three-mile run that was part 
of a semiannual physical fitness test, a spokesman at the Barstow Marine 
Logistics Center said. According to base officials, Darryl Eugene White of 
Montgomery, Ala., was near the halfway point of the run when he collapsed. The 
fitness test consists of pull-ups, sit-ups and the three-mile run, officials 
said. The San Bernardino County coroner's office planned an autopsy. 
</P>
