<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN YSIDRO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 20-year-old woman was killed Wednesday after her car was struck from behind 
on Interstate 5 while visibility was restricted by dense fog, the California 
Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
Celia Perez of Southeast San Diego was northbound on I-5 just south of its 
junction with Interstate 805 at 5:20 a.m. when her car began to have mechanical 
problems, said Lloyd Needham of the CHP. 
</P>
<P>
Perez pulled onto the left-hand shoulder and was slowing when her car was 
struck. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the second car was taken to Scripps Memorial Hospital in Chula 
Vista and treated for cuts and bruises, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Perez's sister, Maria, 22, and her 2-year-old daughter, both of whom were 
passengers, were also treated for bruises at Scripps and released, the 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The accident is under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
Celia Perez was not wearing a seat belt, Needham said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
