<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLIMBERS TRY TO STAY WARM WITH $20 BILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAKE PLACID, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men lost for three days on New York's highest peak where temperatures 
reached 20 below zero said Wednesday they tried unsuccessfully to light fires 
with damp $20 bills and slept in each other's arms to keep warm. 
</P>
<P>
Shawn Dougher, 25, and Ralph Vecchio, 29, both from Stroudsburg, Pa., were in 
stable condition at Lake Placid Memorial Hospital suffering from frostbite. 
</P>
<P>
The men left on a cross-country skiing trip Saturday with plans to reach the 
summit of 5,344-foot Mt. Marcy. They became disoriented because of whiteout 
conditions and remained lost until rescue workers found them Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA030989-0107 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 28513 </DOCID>
