<P>
TALLY OF TEACHERS VOTE DUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Results of balloting by members of the teachers union will be counted Friday, 
although results might not be available until Monday, union officials said. The 
teachers turned out in large numbers at 600 schools on Tuesday to decide on the 
latest contract proposal by the Los Angeles Unified School District, which 
offered a 20% to 24% pay raise over three years. The union is demanding a 21% 
raise over two years and has urged the teachers to reject the latest offer. 
</P>
