<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
'TREE CITY U.S.A.' AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the fourth consecutive year, Beverly Hills has been named "Tree City 
U.S.A." by the National Arbor Day Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills, famous for its abundance of tree species, was given the 
designation because it meets the four municipal tree-care standards established 
by the National Arbor Day Foundation: a legally constituted municipal tree 
organization, a city tree ordinance, a comprehensive community forestry program 
and observance of Arbor Day. 
</P>
