<P>
DRUG CENTER RECEIVES GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New Start, an outpatient counseling center for drug abuse, has been awarded 
$15,500 in matching grant funds by the California Community Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
The 15-year-old center, 2500 Colorado Ave., provides services to individuals 
and groups, has developed outreach programs in middle and high schools, works 
with addicted mothers, maintains a 24-hour hot line, provides community 
speakers and serves as a resource for the courts and social service agencies. 
</P>
<P>
New Start, which must raise funds equal to the grant in order to receive it, 
will hold a benefit March 18. 
</P>
