</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ronnie Harmon testified that his education at the University of Iowa was not a 
joke, as an attorney in the fraud trial of two sports agents questioned the 
running back on why he was allowed to play football despite failing grades. 
</P>
<P>
Harmon, the government's first witness in the trial of Norby Walters and Lloyd 
Bloom in Chicago, acknowledged that he was put on academic probation at the end 
of his junior year and took a summer course in water-color painting, for which 
he got a D. 
</P>
<P>
