<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MATER DEI DEFEATS CORONA DEL MAR, 3-2 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scott Corliss had a no-hitter for 4 2/3 innings and Mater Dei High School went 
on to defeat Corona del Mar, 3-2, in the quarterfinals of the Newport-Mesa 
baseball tournament Wednesday at Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
Corliss (1-0) struck out 10 and didn't allow a hit until Grady Lamar doubled 
with two outs in the fifth. Brian Frankel went the final two innings, striking 
out two, for the save. 
</P>
<P>
The Monarchs (3-1) scored three runs in the fourth. Juan Zarate doubled home 
the first run. Greg Carl and Jeff Chiccarella had run-scoring singles in the 
inning. 
</P>
<P>
Lamar's double in the fifth scored Todd Kerhli, who had walked. Todd Muth had a 
run-scoring double for the Sea Kings in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
In other Newport-Mesa tournament quarterfinal games: 
</P>
<P>
Foothill 13, El Modena 3 -- Corey Parker had two hits, including a key single 
in the top of the fifth, to lead the Knights (2-0) at Foothill. The Knights 
scored six times in the fifth to take a 11-3 lead. Parker had a bases-loaded 
single to drive in two runs and a third run scored on an error on the play. 
Greg Scott pitched five innings for the victory. Scott (1-0) struck out three 
and allowed three runs. Matt Neubrand had two hits and one RBI for El Modena 
(1-3). 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 7, Santa Ana 1 -- Don Disbro had four hits and two RBIs to lead 
the Diablos (2-0) at Mission Viejo. Eric Cedarstaff went six innings, allowing 
two hits, for the victory. Cedarstaff (1-0) struck out five and allowed only an 
unearned run. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin 12, Esperanza 4 -- Shawn Green had two hits and scored three times to 
lead the Tillers (2-)) at Tustin. Monte Jones (1-0) went six innings, striking 
out two, for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
In the consolation round: 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley 4, Estancia 1 -- Mike Mosebrook threw a two-hitter to lead 
the Cougars (2-2) at Estancia. Mosebrook (2-0) struck out six. Buster Nietzke 
had three hits, including a double and a solo home run, for Capistrano Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa 5, Newport Harbor 4 (9 innings) -- Costa Mesa rallied for three runs 
in the top of the seventh to tie the game and scored two in the ninth. Tim 
Yuen's two-run single in the seventh tied it. In the ninth, Hue Kieu tripled in 
a run to give Costa Mesa (1-3) a 4-3 lead. Dave Sallady then singled in Kieu. 
Newport Harbor fell to 0-3-1. 
</P>
<P>
Orange 7, Saddleback 6 -- Jesus Romo tripled in two runs in the bottom of the 
seventh to give the Panthers (1-1) the victory at Corona del Mar High. Romo 
also had a two-run homer. Mike Arroyos had two hits, including a two-run homer 
for Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
In the El Segundo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Edison 6, Long Beach Poly 6 -- Edison advanced to the semifinals because of 
more total bases. J.J. Thobe had three hits, including two home runs, and five 
RBIs for the Chargers (1-0-2). 
</P>
<P>
Westminster 7, Newhall Hart 4 -- Brian Stubbs pitched five innings, allowing 
three hits and a walk and striking out five, for the victory in a quarterfinal 
game at Westminster. Stubbs helped his cause at the plate, with two hits and 
two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
Brea-Olinda 7, Lynwood 2 -- Mike Hudak had two hits and two RBIs for Brea (3-1) 
in a consolation game at Lynwood. Marc Kaiser pitched a four-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
In the Oceanside tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 6, El Camino 2 -- Aaron Scheid pitched a one-hitter to lead the 
Artists (2-0) in a first-round game at El Camino. Scheid struck out five and 
allowed only a third-inning single. Mica Brown had two hits, two runs scored 
and two RBIs for Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague play: 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 9, Rancho Alamitos 5 -- Rudy Lopez had three hits, including two 
doubles, and two RBIs to lead the Tigers (2-0) at Valencia. John Garcia went 
five innings for the victory. Garcia (1-0) struck out five and allowed three 
runs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
