<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Consolidated Seeks Bankruptcy Protection: Consolidated Oil &amp; Gas Inc., 
recently taken over by a group of disgruntled investors, has filed for Chapter 
11 reorganization in U.S. Bankruptcy Court. In its filing, Consolidated listed 
assets of $38.6 million and liabilities of $51.5 million. The Denver company 
has been under financial pressure in recent years because of slumping oil and 
gas prices. In 1987, it reported a $9.3-million loss, compared to a loss of 
$21.5 million the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
