<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sale of Coleco Explored: Coleco Industries Inc.'s board has authorized 
management to look into selling the toy company as a means of solving its 
financial problems, but no potential purchasers have been identified. J. Brian 
Clarke, president and chief executive of the Avon, Conn.-based company that has 
$540.3 million in debts, said the board took the action two weeks ago. The 
committee representing Coleco's creditors in its bankruptcy case has also 
approved exploring a sale, Clarke said. Morton E. Handel, Coleco's chairman, 
said no purchase offers have been received. He wouldn't say whether any talks 
with interested bidders have been held. 
</P>
