<P>
PROSECUTOR SHOOTS SELF TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PLACERVILLE, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dist. Atty. Ronald Tepper of El Dorado County was found shot to death in his 
downtown office today and Placerville Police Chief Bob Harmon said the 
prosecutor committed suicide. 
</P>
<P>
Tepper, 54, was found with a head wound by a district attorney's investigator. 
There was no note explaining the shooting, Harmon said. 
</P>
<P>
Tepper, who was married, had been involved lately in the prosecution of El 
Dorado County Supervisor Michael Visman, who was to be arraigned in U.S. 
District Court in Sacramento later today on marijuana cultivation charges. 
Tepper asked to have the trial shifted from the county to U.S. District Court 
after a challenge to his prosecution of the case. Visman's attorney charged 
that Tepper had a longstanding grudge against his client. He said Tepper 
insisted on going through with a court hearing to review evidence in the case 
to further damage Visman. 
</P>
