KITTY DUKAKIS VOWS ALCOHOL VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kitty Dukakis, wife of Gov. Michael S. Dukakis, said today that she continues 
to fight her alcoholism but plans to resume her busy public life and schedule. 
</P>
<P>
"I am an alcoholic," she told the media at a news conference attended by her 
husband, adding that she hopes the public nature of her visit to a treatment 
center will encourage others to follow her route. "I would have preferred to 
deal with my private trouble in private," she said, acknowledging that was not 
possible as the wife of Massachusetts' governor. "One of the mysteries of this 
disease is that you can have a loving family, a network of caring friends and 
still face recovery every day," she said, asking that she be afforded some 
privacy during the fight. 
</P>
<P>
She returned home Tuesday after spending 31 days at Edgehill Newport, a private 
short-term treatment facility in Rhode Island. 
