<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
'KILL THE UMP, GO TO JAIL' BILL BACKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NASHVILLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With little debate, the Tennessee House voted 95 to 0 today for a bill to 
establish a jail term of up to six months for assaulting a referee or umpire at 
a sports event. The bill is designed to allow schools to prosecute unruly fans 
if the official is not available to file charges. The measure is sponsored by 
Rep. Tommy Head (D-Clarksville). His sister, Pat Head Summitt, is coach of the 
Lady Vols basketball team at the University of Tennessee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
